	year		= {2018},
	month		= {March},
	volume		= {291},
	number		= {4},
	pages		= {593-609},
	pdf			= {spectrum2016.pdf},
	doi			= {http://dx.doi.org/10.1002/mana.201600176},
	abstract	= {<p>In this paper we study the essential spectrum of the operator
\[
L_Au(x)=-(A(x)u'(x))'+u(x)
\]
where \(A(x)\) is a positive absolutely continuous function on \((0,1)\) that resembles \(x^{2\alpha}\) for some \(\alpha\geq 1\). We prove that the essential spectrum of \(L_A\) coincides with the essential spectrum of the operator \(L_\alpha u(x):=-(x^{2\alpha}u'(x))'+u(x)\).</p>},
